---
<ServicePage
  title="Laser Dentistry in Bayside, Queens NY | Thrive Dental"
  description="Laser dentistry in Bayside, Queens NY. Precise, minimally invasive laser treatments for gum disease, oral surgery, and more — less pain and faster healing. Call (718) 225-6677."
  category="Periodontics"
  categoryHref="/services/periodontics"
  h1="Laser Dentistry in Bayside, NY"
  subtitle="Dental lasers allow for incredibly precise treatment with less discomfort, minimal bleeding, and faster healing. We use laser technology for gum treatments, cavity detection, and more."
  heroImg={heroImg}
  overviewTitle="Precision treatment. Less discomfort. Faster healing."
  overviewText="Dental lasers deliver a concentrated beam of light energy that can cut soft tissue, vaporize bacteria, remove diseased cells, and seal blood vessels simultaneously — all with remarkable precision. Because the laser cauterizes as it works, there's minimal bleeding, less post-operative swelling, and in many cases, no sutures are needed. Healing is measurably faster compared to traditional scalpel-based procedures. We use soft-tissue lasers for gum procedures and a separate diode laser for bacterial decontamination in periodontal therapy."
  overviewExtra="Patients from Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck who are candidates for gum surgery often choose laser treatment specifically because of the reduced recovery time. At Thrive Dental, our laser-assisted periodontal therapy targets infected tissue and bacteria in the periodontal pocket without the need for incisions in most cases — which means many patients return to normal activities the same day. We also use laser treatment for frenectomies (tongue and lip ties), gum recontouring, and canker sore or cold sore treatment. If a traditional surgical recommendation has been holding you back from getting your gums treated, ask about whether laser therapy is appropriate for your case."
  benefits={[
    {
      icon: `<path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z"/>`,
      title: 'Minimally Invasive',
      desc: 'Many laser procedures require no scalpel, no sutures, and no stitches — far less invasive than conventional surgery.',
    },
    {
      icon: `<circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M8 14s1.5 2 4 2 4-2 4-2"/><line x1="9" y1="9" x2="9.01" y2="9"/><line x1="15" y1="9" x2="15.01" y2="9"/>`,
      title: 'Faster Recovery',
      desc: 'Laser seals tissue as it works, reducing bleeding and inflammation. Most patients return to normal activity the same day.',
    },
    {
      icon: `<path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>`,
      title: 'Bacterial Precision',
      desc: 'Lasers selectively target bacteria and diseased tissue while leaving healthy tissue intact — more precise than any hand instrument.',
    },
  ]}
  faq={[
    {
      q: 'What conditions can laser dentistry treat?',
      a: 'Gum disease treatment, gum recontouring, frenectomy (tongue and lip ties), canker sore and cold sore treatment, crown lengthening, and cavity detection assistance.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Is laser treatment painful?',
      a: 'Many laser procedures require little or no anesthesia because the laser cauterizes nerve endings as it works. Soft tissue procedures like gum recontouring can often be done with only topical anesthetic.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How does laser gum treatment compare to traditional surgery?',
      a: 'Significantly less invasive. Less bleeding, less post-operative swelling, no sutures in many cases, and faster healing. Most patients return to normal activities the same day.',
    },
    {
      q: 'What is a laser frenectomy?',
      a: 'A laser frenectomy releases a tongue or lip tie — fast, virtually bloodless, no sutures, heals in days. Commonly performed for infants with latch difficulties and for older children and adults with functional restrictions.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Is laser dentistry safe?',
      a: 'Yes. Dental lasers are FDA-cleared and very safe when used by trained clinicians. We provide protective eyewear during all laser procedures and follow strict protocols.',
    },
  ]}
